      <section eId="sec_CHC-1462">
        <num>CHC 1462</num>
        <heading>1462. Â Objection to admission by the minor who has been admitted</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1462__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Objection may be made by the minor who has been admitted if the minor is sixteen years of age or older.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1462__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>If the minor informs any staff person of his desire to object to the admission, a staff person shall assist him in preparing and submitting his objection.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1462__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Upon receipt of an objection, the director of the treatment facility shall release such minor within seventy-two hours unless proceedings are begun pursuant to Chapter 7 or 9 of this Title.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=72958</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
